      "messageBody": "Both defects landed on merge commit 12a4b34e and together failed the\nDesktop Release and CI/CD Pipeline workflows (issue #796).\n\nscripts/install-node-dependencies.sh matched reviewed npm deprecation\nwarnings by exact name@version. Transitive versions float without any\nchange on our side, so when archiver-utils resolved glob from 7.2.3 to\n10.5.0 the warning stopped matching, fell through to the \"unexpected\"\nbucket, and failed the .vsix job plus every desktop build even though\nnpm install itself succeeded. Reviewed deprecations are now matched by\npackage name only, with accurate per-package tracking URLs: glob reaches\nboth workspaces via @link-assistant/web-capture -> archiver ->\narchiver-utils, not via vsce or electron-builder as previously implied.\nUnreviewed diagnostics still fail the build.\n\nscripts/self-hosting-metric.rs read trailers through git's\n%(trailers:key=...) placeholder, which only parses the last paragraph of\na commit message. A release commit that separated Formal-AI-Session and\nFormal-AI-Evidence with a blank line therefore exposed only the evidence\ntrailer, and the resulting \"must record both\" error failed Auto Release\nafter the version had already been computed. Trailers are now read from\nthe full commit body, so placement no longer decides whether a compliant\ncommit is recognised.\n\nBoth suites were confirmed to fail against the pre-fix scripts; the\ntrailer test reproduces the production error string verbatim. Adds\nINSTALL_NODE_DEPENDENCIES_VERBOSE tracing, off by default, and collects\nthe full investigation under dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797.",
