dev/log/issues/796/pulls/797/sessions/b7b0a7df-eaec-4996-8eac-65c1201e46d2/claude-b7b0a7df-eaec-4996-8eac-65c1201e46d2.jsonl:362:{"parentUuid":"4d9a565b-f9d6-4dbe-85e2-f6ce8a9be2e2","isSidechain":false,"message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CdBUfFHuQgLgYoizQA6DL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything is done and verified. Final state:\n\n**PR #797** — [Fix two CI false positives failing the default branch](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/797), ready for review, CI green (run [29687961586](https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/actions/runs/29687961586), all 481 tests passing including both new regression suites).\n\n**Two root causes, both false positives on commit `12a4b34e`:**\n\n- **A** — `install-node-dependencies.sh` allowlisted npm deprecations by exact `name@version`. When `archiver-utils` floated `glob` to `10.5.0`, the warning stopped matching and failed the `.vsix` job plus all four desktop builds, *after* npm itself succeeded. Now matched by package name. The old allowlist also mis-attributed `glob` to electron-builder/vsce; verified against both lockfiles it actually arrives via `@link-assistant/web-capture → archiver → archiver-utils`.\n- **C** — `%(trailers:key=...)` only parses the last paragraph of a commit message, so a blank line between `Formal-AI-Session` and `Formal-AI-Evidence` hid the session trailer and failed Auto Release with \"must record both\" on a commit that recorded both. `trailer_values` now scans the whole body.\n\n**Six upstream issues filed**, each with a reproducible example, workaround and code fix:\n- [web-capture#144](https://github.com/link-assistant/web-capture/issues/144) — I verified `archiver@8.0.0` drops `archiver-utils` entirely for `readdir-glob@^3`, so this is fixable at source, not just suppressible.\n- [rust#97](https://github.com/link-foundation/rust-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/97) / [js#104](https://github.com/link-foundation/js-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/104) / [python#33](https://github.com/link-foundation/python-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/33) — no top-level `permissions:` in `release.yml`\n- [rust#98](https://github.com/link-foundation/rust-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/98) — unretried/unlocked `cargo install rust-script`\n- [python#34](https://github.com/link-foundation/python-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/34) / [rust#99](https://github.com/link-foundation/rust-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template/issues/99) — outdated codecov action\n\nThree things worth flagging rather than glossing over:\n\n1. **The desktop/vsix path did not execute in this CI run.** The `Desktop Release` workflow is `workflow_run`-triggered off main, so no run exists on this branch and zero `npm warn deprecated` lines appear in the logs. Root cause A is covered by unit tests driving the real script against a fake `npm`, but its production path will only be exercised on merge. Same for Auto Release (`skipped` on non-main), which covers root cause C.\n2. **I corrected two of my own earlier claims** after checking the actual upstream files: the `cargo install rust-script` gap is Rust-template-only, not all three, and the glob attribution was wrong in my first draft. Both corrections are recorded in the analysis docs rather than quietly overwritten.\n3. **The template gap analysis found six further gaps** (missing `Cargo.lock` guard job, no post-publish smoke test, no secrets scanning, no fresh-merge simulation, non-resilient Buildx, file-size check skipping `.yml`) that I deliberately did **not** bundle into this PR — they are unrelated to the #796 failures. A recommended landing order is in `template-gap-analysis.md` §4 if you want those as follow-ups."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":692,"cache_read_input_tokens":60100,"output_tokens":1272,"s